description:
Hal Jordan resumes his career as the Green Lantern while trying to rebuild his personal life.

After some soul searching Hal Jordan goes to the JLA headquarters in New York City, where much to the team's objects, he informs them that he is not coming back to the JLA but wants to tell Guy Gardner to be a better Lantern, for the Corps sake.

After saying goodbye to Batman, Hal takes a train, hobo style, to Hope Springs, a small town that is in process of transforming from a mining town to a farming town. There Hal searches out Rose Lewis, who since last he saw her got married and changed her name to Rose Hardin. Hal also learns that she is now a widow and single mother or Toby Hardin.

Hal convinces her to give him a job on the ranch and she seems to fall for his charm and attitude toward Toby. After a few days, Hal feels better about himself, but then Guy shows up to ruin it. Guy tricks Hal into using his ring and revealing to Rose that Hal is really the Green Lantern, who years earlier came to Hope Springs and sided with the Mining company that killed her husband. Hal tries to plead with Rose but she won't hear any of it, and he is forced to leave town.

Meanwhile John Stewart, believes himself going insane and tries to contact Appa Ali Apsa, but to no avail. John then flies to Oa where he sees the planet is still in ruin and can't find the last Guardian. Just when he thinks of giving up, he finds the dead body of Priest.

description:
Hal continues to try and find a place in the world that doesn't include him being the Green Lantern. Meanwhile, Guy Gardner comes face-to-face with the Tattoo Man and he just might need Jordan's help. Plus, John Stewart's journey to OA takes an unexpected turn. "Pursuit of Happiness!" Part 2 of 8. Guest-starring Green Lantern (Guy Gardner) and Green Lantern (John Stewart).

Hal Jordan is on the continued mission to find peace in the world and his road has led him to a small fishing village. There he gets a job on a fishing boat and works with a man named Clay who has his own views on life.

Meanwhile in New York City, Guy Gardner gets bored hanging out at the JLA headquarters and goes out into the city to find some actions. While at the Palace of Fine Arts, a tattoo parlor, Guy finds the Tattooed Man working as a tattoo artist. Guy tries to get the Tattooed Man to fight him but Tarrant claims to have gone legit. Guy fallows Tarrant home and keeps trying to egg him on and when he makes fun of Tarrant's mother Tarrant attacks.

The pair fight through out the city and Guy leads him out to sea, and by using his ring to track Hal, Guy leads the Tattooed Man to the small fishing village Hal is in. Hal sensing Guy is nearby tries to divert the fight but is himself drawn into it and knocked in to a neighborhood dinner, where he is seen by Clay.

Hal defeats Tarrant and is angry with Guy for making him fight Guy's battles. Guy goes back to New York, leaving the Tattooed Man to be dealt with by the "hicks". When Hal returns to the fishing vessel the captain now knowing that Hal is the Green Lantern wants nothing to do with the hero, and Hal is forced to leave another town due to Guy.

Later Tarrant wakes up on the beach and is offered Hal's old job.

Meanwhile on Oa, John Stewart learns the Old Timer, killed Priest and is gone insane. John tries to escape Oa but the Old Timer cuts him off, leaving John trapped.

Notes:

  • The cover was signed Broderick and Nelson but in the letter column it stated that Pat Broderick did the cover himself.
  • First letter column title "Green Lantern."
  • First post-Crisis appearance of the Tattoo Man.

description: When Hal finally has enough of Guy's constant needling the two Lanterns fight it out without power rings. Both fighters are promptly arrested by a small town sheriff who later lets the Lanterns go in exchange for their help in dealing with two drunken townies who have gone wild with Hal and Guy's power rings. Meanwhile the insane Guardian Appa Ali Apsa continues his torment of John Stewart while using his awesome power to tear cities from their home worlds and fuse them into a Mosaic World.

description:
Hal decides to investigate the sudden disappearances of two entire towns. Meanwhile, John Stewart plans to escape his malevolent tormentor, even if it costs him his life. "Among my Souvenirs!" Part 4 of 8. Guest-starring Green Lantern (Guy Gardner) and Green Lantern (John Stewart). Justice League cameo.

Hal Jordan has gotten a job in California as a peach picker and life couldn't be more complete, but unknown to him, Appa Ali Apsa is stealing cities that he has been to. His latest being is Evergreen City.

Later after having a conversation with Clay about running from things you believe own you Hal decides not to charge his ring anymore and just be a normal person. That night Hal has a nightmare where John Stewart is telling him to protect the cities but all Hal can do is pick peaches.

When Hal wakes up Clay tells him about the missing cities and Hal realizes the next town will be Hope Springs and flies there to stop it from being taken. When he gets there he is too late and it is gone. Hal knowing what to do charges his ring, by using the oath he hasn't said in months and flies off to Oa to stop the Mad Guardian.
name: Among My Memories

description:
Hal races to the planet OA to save the displaced Earth cities. But does even the Green Lantern have enough will power to defeat a Guardian gone mad? Especially when his immortal adversary offers him the life he always wanted. "Back Again!" Part 5 of 8. Guest-starring Green Lantern (Guy Gardner) and Green Lantern (John Stewart).

Hal Jordan is flying to Oa to stop Appa Ali Apsa from stealing cities and their inhabitants from Earth when he runs into an invisible force field and is knocked unconscious.

When Hal wakes up he is in the presence of Rose and Toby Hardin in what appears to be Hope Springs. Rose blames Hal for their kidnapping but before Hal can explain they hear a scream from outside. When Hal checks on it some farmers have cornered a group of Xudarians. Hal rescues the aliens and uses the ring to translate their language and learns that they walked from their city to Hope Springs.

Hal then leaves Hope Spring to confront Appa Ali Apsa, and along the way he sees many other life forms. One he meets is aggressive against him and when it appears the alien has defeated him Appa shows up and tells Hal either he keeps him company of Appa will kill him.

Hal then wakes up again in the Hardin house, but this time Rose and Toby act like they are back on Earth and Hal believes them. Then that night, Hal's ring gives off a spark and wakes Hal from the illusion of being on Earth. Hal then pretends to go to bed but instead sends a message to Guy Gardner to come to Oa to stop Appa Ali Apsa.

Notes:

  • Last letter column titled "Green Lantern."
name: Back Again

description:
Guy arrives on Oa, but will his presence save the day, or just make things worse. Plus, what will be the cost for the mad Guardian's patchwork world? "Two Against the World!" Part 6 of 8. Guest-starring Green Lantern (Guy Gardner) and Green Lantern (John Stewart).

Guy Gardner is flying to Oa to help Hal Jordan stop Appa Ali Apsa and his mad plan to steal cities and move them to Oa, but as Guy nears Oa he gets a message from Hal to sneak in quietly. Guy does this by stowing away on a city from Barrio III, which Appa is bring to Oa.

Meanwhile on Oa, John Stewart is trying to fight the mental control Appa has on him but no avail and Hal Jordan gets in contact with Tomar Tu, who agrees to help the Green Lantern.

When Guy gets to Oa, he emerges from his hiding spot, but is attacked by the residents of the Barrio city, due to the fact they are under Appa's mind control. Guy escapes the city but is attacked at every turn by different alien creatures. Lucky for Guy, Hal uses his ring to project different creatures to scare off the aliens that are attacking Guy, but soon Guy's luck runs out and he is captured by Appa.

While Guy is trying to get to John and Hal, Hal uses a trick and enters the broken power battery but when he emerges he is captured by Appa. Appa tries to read Hal's mind and learn of Hal's plans but can't. Appa soon looses interest in Hal's plans and reveals the next stage in his plan it to destroy the home world of the cities he stole and use their power to make his Mosaic World permanent.

Notes:

  • First letter column titled "Oa, By the Way...."
name: Two Against the World

description:
Hal, Guy, and John are all at the mercy of the mad Guardian. Who will save the day now? The answer may surprise you. "Homecoming!" Part 7 of 8. Guest-starring Green Lantern (Guy Gardner) and Green Lantern (John Stewart).

Guy Gardner, John Stewart and Hal Jordan are all at the mercy Appa Ali Apsa, the last remaining Guardian in the Universe. Appa tortures Hal by forcing him to watch helplessly as Appa mind controlled aliens attack the Xudarians for helping Hal. Then Hal is forced to watch as Appa turns his beasts on Rose and Toby Hardin. Just as Appa is about to give the final blow to Hal, the Guardians of the Universe return to Oa.

It is then revealed that Hal earlier went into the broken Power Battery not to get power but to contact the Guardians and let them know of Appa's plans and misdeeds. The Guardians deal with the Mad One while Hal and the other two lanterns rescue the people in danger.

Just when it appears like the heroes have saved the day, John becomes mind controlled again and goes to Appa's aide leaving Hal and Guy to deal with Appa's beasts. Soon their rings become drained and they realize the Guardians have been defeated and Appa Ali Apsa is now the most powerful being in the Universe.

description:
The Guardians have fallen before the unparallel might of one of their own. Can the trio of Green Lanterns from Earth - the optimistic Hal Jordan, the obnoxious Guy Gardner, and the stalwart John Stewart, somehow muster enough will power to defeat the malevolent immortal before it's too late? "Bringing it Together!" Part 8 of 8. Guest-starring Green Lantern (Guy Gardner) and Green Lantern (John Stewart).

Guy Gardner and Hal Jordan are on Oa facing a army of Appa Ali Apsa's mind controlled creatures, and their rings are drained of their power, so Hal proposes a bluff that doesn't seem to be working. Then the Xudarians, led by Tomar Tu and the people of Hope Springs led by Rose Hardin come to the rescue.

Hal and Guy use one of the Xudarian's speeders to find Pazu Pinder Pol, one of the Guardians who are battling Appa for the fate of Oa, and convince him to change tactics while they find John Stewart.

Pazu agrees and instead of trying to say Oa the Guardians began to attack it. This confuses Appa and gives Hal time to find John, who is mind linked with Appa. Hal has John go into Appa's mind and show him great loneliness. This cause Appa to release his hold on the power of Oa long enough for the Guardians to take control of it and turn it on Appa, killing him.

Later, Hal, Guy and John stand in-front of the Guardians who inform them that they will be reforming the Corp and each of the three will have a part. John feels better now that the voices in his head are gone, Guy feels angry knowing Hal will get the cushy job while he's going to have to work, and Hal feels better knowing he is both Hal Jordan and Green Lantern.
name: Bringing it Together

description:
Oa-The Guardians give their orders to the Green Lanterns of Earth. Hal Jordan is tasked with finding suitable candidates to rebuild the Corps, John Stewart has been appointed the protector and caretaker of the Mosaic World, and Guy Gardner is finally named the sole Green Lantern of Space Sector 2814.

Earth-Guy tries inform The Justice League International that he is the new and only Green Lantern of Earth but no one believes him. He then goes across the globe trying to be a Green Lantern, the Guy Gardner way. He averts a mid-air collision by destroying one of the planes, he wreaks the home a man that kinda looks like someone who might work for the mob, and he brings a taste of the USA to Bulbania, the last commie place, that Guy knows of.

While planing on saving the dolphins, Guy is blindsided by G'nort, who tries to convince Guy that he was given a ring by the Guardians and was told to patrol any sector he wants and he choose 2814. This does not sit well with Guy who tries to get rid of G'nort, but the alien is persistent and forces Guy to call the Guardians and see what they have to say.

The Guardians claim to have nothing to do with G'nort and order Guy to let him stay in Sector 2814 until they can learn who gave him the ring. Guy, not wanting to be attached to G'nort and longer then he has to be, takes G'nort with him off world to find these Guardians who gave him the ring.

description:
Just who is G"nort? Where did he get his ring? Who was this mysterious Uncle? And what does all this have to do with the Weaponers of ....? Never mind. Part 2 of three of a Guy and His G'nort.

Guy is determined to get rid of G'Nort and drags his unwanted new partner to G'Nort's homeworld in hopes of finding out just who exactly entrusted a power ring to such a "bonehead". But things take a more dangerous turn when Guy discover the Weaponer of Qward may be behind his new "friends" sudden induction into the Corps.
name: Bring in the Clowns

description: Say hello to the Poglachian Green Lantern Corps the most ridiculous group ever to wield a power ring! Armed with the emerald energy and a mandate to "do whatever you want" the Poglachians Corps have secretly been assembled by the Weaponers of Qward in an effort to embarrass and disgrace the Green Lantern name before the new Corps can be born. Guy is forced to battle these witless "Green Lanterns", however his efforts may be hampered by the "help" of his new partner, the bumbling G'Nort.
name: Fools Rush In

description:
The conclusion of "A Guy and His G'Nort": the threat from the Weaponers of Qward has suddenly gotten real and Guy faces certain death unless his new "partner" G'Nort can save the day. But can G'Nort, who has failed at everything in his life, find it within himself to master a power ring and save his "best pal Guy" before it's too late?

Notes:

  • Cover credits Bruce Patterson while creator data credits Pablo Marcos as the inker.

description:
Hal Jordan, Guy Gardner, and John Stewart set out to reform the legendary Green Lantern Corps. Plus, witness the unimaginable - the Guardians laugh. "Core...!" Guest-starring Green Lantern (Guy Gardner) and Green Lantern (John Stewart). Cameos by Blue Beetle and Fire.

Notes:

  • Chapter I: "The Chore..."
  • Chapter II: "The Core..."
  • Chapter III: "The Corps..."
  • Pages 1, 26-38 penciled by M. D. Bright and inked by Romeo Tanghal.
  • Pages 2-13 penciled by Joe Staton and inked by Bruce Patterson.
  • Pages 14-25 penciled and inked by Pat Broderick.

description:
Mosaic: Part 1 of 4. "Structures!" Starring Green Lantern (John Stewart). John Stewart is in charge of looking over the new Oa. But Oa has become a melting pot of differences. What do you do when different kinds of life-forms needing different kinds of things for survival collide.

Notes:

  • Martian Manhunter cameo flashback appearance.

description: Mosaic: Part 4 of 4. "Structures!" Starring Green Lantern (John Stewart). Guest-starring Green Lantern (Hal Jordan). The Mosaic is coming apart at the seems and John Stewart is the only one who can hold it together. Plus, the Guardians reveal their intentions and John is not happy about it. Don't miss a major turning point in the life of this Green Lantern. NOTE: John Stewart's mission continues in Green Lantern: Mosaic.

description: Hal Jordan and Guy Gardner put their respective Green Lantern rings on the line in a fight to determine who will be earth's Green Lantern. The younger and stronger Gardner delivers a brutal beating to Jordan who appears to be going down. Unknown to Gardner, Jordan pulled a "rope-a-dope" allowing Gardner to tire himself out. Jordan then doled out his own punishment, knocking out Gardner and taking his ring from him. This story propelled Guy Gardner in a new direction, seeking out Sinestro's former yellow ring.
name: Prize Fight

description:
Hal Jordon finds himself on Rann being held captive by Adam Strange for the kidnapping of Aleea. Hal has no memory of doing this nor how or why he is on Rann. Then when Adam says something about earth all the memories flood back the Green Lantern. About how he had lunch with a back from the dead Barry Allen. About how he was going to give an answer to Carol Ferris's marriage proposal. And about how Olivia Reynolds hired him to fly her to a mystery meeting in the desert. This last memory made Hal realize that Olivia had made him go to Rann to kidnap Aleea and take her to the Antimatter Universe.

Hal makes a deal with Adam to help him rescue Aleea from the Qwards but when they get to the Qwards universe they find and all out war and Olivia has Aleea and has made herself Queen of Qward.
name: Life Decisions

description: Hal Jordon and Adam Strange find them on Qward battling the Qwardians and Olivia Reynolds, who is under the influence of the U-mind. She uses her powers to capture Hal but Adam is able to get away with the help of his daughter, Aleea. Olivia is planning on giving Hal over to the Qwardians, who want to kill him him, when Adam and Aleea get to her. Aleea uses her U-mind power against Olivia's, and with some help from Hal's green lantern power she is able to beat Olivia. Seeing there new queen defeated by the all powerful Green Lantern, the Qwards let the heroes go free. Once back at Rann Hal mind erases Olivia and takes her back to earth promising Adam that Olivia will not be a threat to Aleea ever again.
name: Life Forces

description:
Barry Allen has recently returned from the dead and is running mayhem over Keystone City, and Hal Jordan has put it upon himself to stop his old friend. But not only does he need to contend with the speedster, the Darkstar Ferrin, feel that the Flash needs to be stopped, at all costs.

Hal and Barry have an all out battle in the Flash Museum, but just when it looks like the Flash is going to kill Hal, Darkstar steps in and appairently kills Barry, again. After Hal and Darkstar have a brief argument and go there respective way Barry reveals that he was hidding under ground.

Once Hal goes back to Carol Ferris, who has been acting strange that past couple of days it is revealed that the Predator has finally escaped being trapped inside Carol.
name: A Flash Of Evil

description:
The Predator has been forced from Carol Ferris's mind and body, and attacks Hal Jordon. The two fight and just as it looks that the Predator has the upper hand his power fades just enough for Hal and Carol to escape. Hal flys to Tom's house, there he explains to Tom that something is wrong with Carol, and Tom would need to watch the air taxi for a little while, Tom tries to explain to Hal that some one is secretly funding the Air taxi but Hal as no time and leaves. While at Tom's house Hal ignores Arisia, who is still in love with the Green Lantern.

The Predator sees Arisia and the anger towards Hal and Carol that she possesses. This makes it easy for him to possess her and he uses her body to track Hal and Carol to a cabin north of where Evergreen used to be. There the Predator attacks Hal but the fight is intrupted by Deathstroke who tells Hal that after he takes care of the Predator "your next".
name: Predators and Prey

description:
The Predator has been forced out of Carol Ferris's pyche, and is now using Arisia's body to track down Carol and Hal Jordon. The Predator has found Hal at his cabin north of Evergreen, but Deathstroke has been hired to track down Carol and protect her, at any costs. While Hal and the Predator fight Deathstroke escapes with Carol as a hostage.

Hal chases after Deathstroke but the assasin is much too slippery for the Green Lantern. But when he comes face to face with the Predator, Deathstroke may have met his match.

Meanwhile, inside the Predator pyche Arisia regains her lost memories, and discovers that traped inside the Predator is the Star Saphire, and she has a dark secert. Arisia with the help of the Star Saphire are able to expel the Predator back into Carol's body and let the Star take control and destroy the Predator.

This is where is it is revealed the the Star Saphire is pregnant but it will not give birth for a while. Deathstroke decides that he is being played and doesn't need this job and leaves Hal, Arisia and Carol to figure out what to do next.
name: Death Times Two

description:
Hal Jordan's old friend Itty returns and asks a favor of the Green Lantern of earth. Itty's bride is about to give "birth" and Itty is needed in space to stop an Laroo armada that has come to earth to kill the Lasma couple, and end there race forever.

While Hal is trying to protect Itty's bride, a ground force of Laroo are able to destroy Hal's Power Battery, and Hal is forced to absorb all the power for the battery. This causes him to possess great power for a limited time. He uses this to help Itty defeat the armada. Back on earth Itty's bride has the offspring and puts them into Hal's care while Itty and her take care of something.

Meanwhile on earth, Carol Ferris and Tom Kalmaku both discover, some one is try to sabotaoge Hal's life on earth.
name: Perilous Nativity

description:
Trinity: Part 5. "Turf War!" Guest-starring Lobo, L.E.G.I.O.N., and the Darkstars. Story continued from Darkstars (1992-1996 DC) #11. With the fate of the Guardians hanging in the balance, the Green Lantern Corps face off with L.E.G.I.O.N. and the Darkstars in a battle royal for the right to save the universe. Plus, the tomb of the Triach's terrible creator is discovered and this could mean the end of everything! Story continues in L.E.G.I.O.N. (1989-1994 1st Series) #58.

description:
Reign of the Supermen tie-in. "Death City!" Guest-starring Superman, Superboy, Supergirl (Matrix) and Steel. Hal returns from his ordeal in space to find Coast City destroyed. With everything he cared about gone, Green Lantern faces the culprits responsible - the sinister Cyborg Superman and the immensely powerful Mongul. Steel and Supergirl have already fallen, is Green Lantern next? Don't miss the tale that changes Hal Jordan's life forever!

Notes:

  • "DC Universe 13" one page featuring a Zero Hour teaser.
  • Story continues from Superman: The Man of Steel #26.
  • Superman continues in Superman #82.

description:
"This is Now!" Guest-starring Green Arrow. Back together again, Green Lantern and Green Arrow team-up to take on the intergalactic merc Flicker and discover the mystery behind Carol Ferris' connection to the Crosswinds Corporation once and for all.

Oliver Queen was in Star City fighting Flicker in an alley. Flicker quickly defeats the archer and knocking him out. After meeting Carol Ferris, Hal Jordan found out Oliver and Tom Kalmaku had disappeared after she had fund Hal's air taxi business using the Crosswinds Corp. and drawing connections to a place that Olivia Reynolds is heading, Crosswinds Corner where a large castle stands. Hal flies Carol over but are attacked along the way by missiles. They enter the castle by going through a window and Carol reveals that her father, Carl Ferris is alive when he appears in front of Hal and attacks him relentlessly and Hal fights back to hurt him but breaks the shell of Carl Ferris who's a robot but Carol is kidnapped by Flicker who drags her to another room placing her with Tom as well as the newly arrived Olivia lead by another of the Carl Ferris robots. Hal notices Carol's disappearance and sets out to find her, instead meets Oliver who compares their days in Hard Traveling Heroes to their modern days which lead to a brief argument between the two who focuses on how to rescue their friends which came up with pretending to harm Carol which leads to the robots turning on Flicker who escapes and seeing Carol's mother who was alive and everyone going to their own paths. Olivia drove away to sell her toys when she noticed a statue of Hal as Green Lantern losing his head...
name: This is Now

description:
Mourning the destruction of Coast City, Hal Jordan uses his power ring to resurrect his home town and its inhabitants including his parents and his childhood girlfriend, Jennifer. However, it all suddenly fades away, and Hal finds himself face to face with a Guardian who wants him to surrender his ring, as he has violated their most sacred canon by using the ring for personal gain.

Coast city has been vaporized, not nothing more than a rather large hole or charred sand. Hal is there, grieving, thinking about why his city was destroyed and thinking of all his life has been and how all of it is tied into this city.now a simple hole.

He uses his ring to recreate coast city and speaks with his dad and mom and even his very first girlfriend. Alas the people were not truly reborn but simple manifestations of his battered Psyche. Just as his father is about to tell him what he has always wanted to hear, his ring runs out of power.

A guardian appears before him demanding he hand over his ring and prepare to be transported back to Oa where he will go on trial for using his ring for personal gain. Grief stricken Hal has other ideas and refuses to wield the ring, he absorbs the power of the guardians projection and decides he will have the power he needs so he can set things right.

Meanwhile Kyle Rayner and his girlfriend Alex Dewitt enjoy a moonlight romp on the beach, they both see a green star ascending to the heavens, at Alexs behest Kyle makes a wish on the star.
name: Emerald Twilight, Part 1: The Past

description:
Driven mad by the destruction of his city, Hal Jordan hell bent on its resurrection cuts a swath through the remaining Green Lantern corp in his bid for more power. As he gets closer to Oa and defeats his fellow Corps men he adds their rings to his. All this and on Oa the guardians are forced to make a fateful decision to safeguard there very survival......reinstate Sinestro of Korugar as leader of the green lantern corp since he alone stands a chance of stopping Hal!

Hal Jordan once the greatest green lantern is full of rage as he flies off toward the planet Oa. As he gets closer hes confronted by a series of lanterns, from Kehaan and Laira to Tomar Tu, Hannu, Jack T chance, Boodika and even Kilowog. With each fight his rage increases as he thinks about all hes given to the corps, to the guardians and to the galaxy as a whole and all he has to show for it is a charred piece of land where his life once stood. He also adds each defeated Lanterns rings to his hand, thus increasing his powers.

Meanwhile on Oa the guardians are confident that one of there servants will stop Jordan, Ganthet is the lone voice of reason pleading they try an alternate course of action as what they are trying will not work. With no plan of their own as Jordan is almost upon Oa and more powerful than ever they decide to do as Ganthet suggests.

As Jordan arrives the guardians make one finale plea for him to surrender his ring when he refuses and demands the power of the central battery, their midnight savior approaches and its revealed as.SINESTRO!!!!
name: Emerald Twilight, Part 2: The Present

description:
Hal Jordan's quest for power concludes as he faces off with his former mentor and friend Sinestro. Words are not enough to turn back this self made hero as he kills Sinestro and his longtime mentor Kilowog. He then takes the life of every Guardian but not before Ganthet travels to Earth with one finale edict from his fallen comrades find a new Green Lantern.

Hal and Sinestro face of with the fate all Oa itself and the central battery at risk. Sinestro convinces Hal to discard the extra rings so they can settle this man to man. Hal accepts and they duel as the Guardians watch on. They seem evenly matched as Sinestro taunts Jordan that he sinestro was the greatest green lantern the world universe had ever seen, how the guardians begged him to mold Jordan into a semblance of him though Jordan was never worthy then and not now. All this fuels Hals rage an he lashes out with his power. They reach a stalemate and engage in hand to hand combat. Sinestro continues to taunt Hal till he finally snaps his neck.

Killowog then attacks his friend and makes one last attempt to reach him. In the end Hal incinerates him and discards the ring. Surrounded by the guardians they prepare to punish him but because they dont normally take matters into their own hands they allow him to go straight for the central power battery.

Ganthet pleads with them until they finally decide to do something. They focus their life energy into him just as Hal absorbs all the power of Oa. When hes done he steps out in his parallax suit past the dead guardians, stepping on a green lantern ring before flying off.

Ganthet then emerges from the bodies and creates a ring from the energy he was granted. He then teleports to Earth. On earth Kyle sees a similar green star to the one he saw ascending a few issues back except this time it descends. It almost crashes into him an out pops ganthet. He gives Kyle the ring and departs. Once hes gone Kyles tries on the ring and becomes GL for the first time, in the classic lantern suit.
name: Emerald Twilight, Part 3: The Future

description:
It's green lantern like you've never seen before as Ganthet locates Kyle Rayner, a struggling earth based artist and hands him the most powerful weapon in the universe...the last Lantern Ring....All this and he battles the deadly Ohm.

Elsewhere Mongul escapes from the cyborg superman and vows revenge on the Green Lantern....

Its the aftermath of Kyle getting the ring, so he hops over to his girlfriend house to tell her the big news. They reconcile their differences, having broken up a week before because of Kyles apparent irresponsibility. She props him up on the couch as the bedroom is still off limits and they sleep. In the morning she wakes up first grabs her camera and gets a radio beat on a villain whos stolen some electrical armor from Star labs. She rouses Kyle and they take off.

Once their she tells Kyle to stay put as she will just take a few pictures and then they can take off. Kyle thinks about staying put but decides to instead play hero and flies off after the villain. He gets pummeled as he gets used to flying and creating constructs. In the end though he beats the villain cuts him out of the suit, saves the city and gets some damn fine pictures taken of him being all heroic.

The crowd though mistakes him for Hal with a different hair color, since he is in Hals suit. Alex Pulls him away and they go for a walk on the beach at sunset. After they talk a bit she tells him to change his costume since its not really His. He does and we get the iconic fish mask classic edition Kyle suit! Sweeet

Back at the Slab a prison for super villains the guards get slaughtered by Mongul who swears to kill Green lantern and Superman!
name: It All Begins Here

description:
Kyle our new hero is caught in the clutches of the vengeful Mongul who doesn't care that this is not hal he just want green lantern's head on a shiny new platter, will kyle survive? find out inside!

Kyle and Alex are on the beach so she can take some pictures of him for the press, to get his identity and profile out there. This of course boosts both their career; his heroing and her photography. Once thats done they decide to check out what the ring can really do, he test out his flying then tries to create something he has intimate knowledge of.he creates Alex in a very revealing swimsuit, much to her chagrin (lol). She asks if the ring has the same energy as last time he says yeah, it just keeps going and going, hell hes been using it for three days now with no ill effects. He then creates weapons and shield since hell need them in battle. Once he makes a laser blaster which pretty much nearly kills them though Kyle thinks its so cool.

Mongul meanwhile continues his escape. He kills and alien who was giving him praise simple because he didnt like his race, he then unleashes all the prisoners so the guards cant effectively stop him. He then corners a guard with a flying apparatus and questions the location of superman and Green Lantern, the guard has no idea where supes is but says GL was spotted in L.A. he kills the guard grabs the jet pack and takes off for L.A.

The red head guys from the alley where Kyle first got the ring is meeting with a shady character telling him what happened in the alley and then hands over a glowing green rock that he found on site. He asks for money in exchange for the rock. He gets his throat cut as the mysterious man yes the green glowing rock.

Back on the beach Alex and Kyle are cooling off from the test and training when Kyle quickly pushes Alex aside as Mongul descends on them. Mongul thinks Kyle is Hal so he betas him severely and even plans to kill Alex cause shes GL lady. Kyle gets pummeled as a terrified Alex watches on
name: Breaking In

description:
Kyle is about to die when SUPERMAN comes to his rescue. While supes tangles with Mongul. Kyle is roused by Alex and jumps right back into the fight, only to be tossed away like so much trash. Supes and mongul continue to battle as Alex worries for Kyle. Kyle jumps back in the fight again and send Mongul flying. While the trio fights Supes wants to know who Kyle is, Kyle says GL obviously, supes says not the one I know. They banter about Mongul and his mad on for GL the old one. Supes says Mongul doesnt really care if hes the same guy he just wants to kill him.

Supes takes over the battle as Kyle gets his bearings, Alex eggs him on to do something BIG. While hes kinda in awe that THE superman is here helping him. In the end Kyle drops Mongul with a well placed subway train that literally steal rolls him. Supes commends him on his ring skills despite Kyles obliviousness to who the guardians and the corps. are. Supes say link him whenever hes in Metroplis and Alex and Kyle watch supes carry off Mongul to parts unknown. Kyle realizes he really can do this hero bit

Back at creepy place the dude who got the green rock has tried everything to cut it, dissect it, or just test the darn thing to no avail. He turns it over to Major force and hands him a file with all the info gathered on the new GL. Major force only wants to know, do they want just the ring or his whole hand?
name: Rematch

description:
Our story starts with Kyle and Alex arriving home from dinner, courtesy of his ring, they do the whole superhero flight. Alex loves it though she has to chide Kyle first. Once inside she jumps out of her clothes and beckons Kyle to the bedroom, hes not in the doghouse anymore. He quickly follows her into the bedroom.

Major Force is on a plane to L.A. Hes being prepped by some suit, who has the audacity to imply hes dumb. Major Force squeezes the suit's throat and gives him a stern warning not to do that $hit again. They then descend on L.A with him having all the info he needs to locate Alex.

At home Alex takes a shower while Kyle watches TV. He realizes a series of bizarre happenings are occurring in L.A. and Alex tells him to go do the hero thing. He wants her to come with him she declines, but promises that she will have a surprise for him when he gets back. He blasts off to L.A. where a city from the future has materialized. An earthquake starts and Kyle has to save the whole city. Back at home Alex hears a knock at the door. She answers the door and is quickly attacked by Major Force who asks her where her boyfriend is. He chases her to the kitchen where she tries to cut him with a knife. It breaks on his chest and he starts to beat her up and questions her again. When she doesnt comply he stranglers her. After she dies he moves off her body. Kyle saves the future city and they all disappear to their correct time lines. Kyle flies back home ready for his present.

When Kyle arrives home he sees a note on the table, his present is in the fridge, he goes to the kitchen only to find Alexs mutilated and contorted body stuffed into the fridge. Kyle freaks out and Major Force walks in beckoning he hand over the ring and get a quick death. Major Force also boasts hes the one who killed Alex. Kyle blasts him out of the building and in a rage he injures the villain and proceeds to almost kill him. At the last moment his ring runs out of power, Kyle is in shock as Major Force descends on him.

End of issue
name: Forced Entry

description:
Kyle is being brutally assaulted by Major Force since his ring has no power. Despite this he does not back down. Major Force continues his beating until pulling out the green rock to get some answers before killing Kyle. The green rock charges Kyles ring and forms itself into a power battery. With his powers restored he steamrolls Major force then has him strapped into an electric chair so he can get some answers about who sent him and why Alex was killed.

Right before he can get those answers police arrive and try to take Kyle in, hes in no mood to be trifled with so he tells them MF killed Alex and thats all they need to known they try to take him in but he flies off. He stops on a roof, confused, angry, hurt and regretting ever accepting the power ring. He goes to his apartment where he meets Alan Scott. He lashes out at Allan thinking him another assassin. Allan calms him down and tells him the history of the Green Lantern Corps. and Hals descent into villainy. Kyle is thankful for the info but needs time to be alone. Allan leaves him to grieve and process all he info.

Kyle then decides not to get rid of the ring because Alex wouldnt want him to, he decides to press on despite the pain he feels to make her proud. Right then Metron and Superman arrive before him, hes being recruited to stop Parallax.

Notes:

  • "DC Universe 19" one page advertisement piece with information on the upcoming Zero Hero mini-series. Plus, San Diego Comic-Con 1994. Included are dates, times and location of the convention.
  • Nearly all Green Lanterns have a cameo flashback appearance.

description: A Zero Month crossover issue. After the events of Zero Hour #0, Green Lantern Kyle Rayner and Parallax Hal Jordan are locked in combat. A tunnel carries them through time and space to present-day Oa, which still shows the debris caused by Emerald Twilight. Face to face with the destruction he has wrought, and powerless due to his energies being drained during Zero Hour, Hal stops fighting. Hal appeals to Kyle, asking him to give one more chance to be a hero. The two share a moment where they come to understand each other, and Kyle gives Hal his ring. Hal immediately begins to misuse the power, and Kyle tries to get it back. Hal attacks a powerless Kyle, who is forced to escape into the labyrinths beneath OA. Stumbling upon the resting place of deceased Green Lantern Corpsmen, Kyle sets am ambush and gets his ring back. Now re-powered, Hal attacks, but Kyle decides to destroy Oa instead. Hal tries to stop him, but Kyle is successful in destroying Oa. Kyle appears to be the sole survivor, and heads back to Earth.

description:
In the aftermath of his epic showdown with the Parallax, Kyle has earned the malign attention of the dread lord of Apokolips himself, Darkseid.

After the events of Zero Hour Kyle finds himself stranded on an alien planet unable to get home, hell he doesnt even know which direction home is!

He enters an alien bar and asks direction back to earth, an alien chick throws herself at him he turn her down but her alien boyfriend attacks him anyway. He thrashes him and then more bar matrons attack. He is saved by a woman with green skin bearing the symbol of the Green Lantern Corp. They flee to a rooftop where they can be alone. She reminisces about being a lantern and missing it, Kyle consoles her having lost Alex they find solace in each other and kiss. When Kyle wakes up Dara is gone as is his ring.

He cant locate her so he goes back to the bar where he finally realizes where she is. He confronts her and she hands him back the ring since it does not work for her, Kyle offers to take her with him where they can start a new life. She refuses and tells him to leave as he walks off she shoots herself in the head, hara kiri has occurred. Kyle is shaken by this turn of events.

He laments how many people keep dying because of his ring as he leaves the planet, he wonders if he will ever find his way home and comes smack dab in front of a big ole spaceship.

description:
Green Lantern relocates to the Big Apple. Unfortunately for the neophyte hero, his mind is taken over by the mental powers of the devious Psimon.

Kyle has made it back to earth and is at Alexs grave telling her goodbye. He has decided to move to new York as they had originally planned, he has work and an apartment lined up so he tells her goodbye tearfully and departs.

In new York in the hustle and bustle Kyle is admittedly lost, he gets directions from a friendly man and is beset by a crazy man. He meets his landlord and then sets up shop in his apartment and finishes his work. Once thats done psimon attacks hes incorporeal so Kyle cant harm him. He takes over Kyless body and attacks the teen titans
name: Farewells

description:
A rift in space and time is allowing demonic creatures access to the world of man. Can Kyle figure out a way to stop this madness before these bizarre creatures overrun mankind?

Kyle meets up with Donna Troy his new teammates since hes gotten into the Titans. She helps him unpack the rest of his things and help set up his apartment. They flirt a little and clearly have more than just physical attraction going on. He even entrusts her with his secret identity. They share their history with each other; dead girlfriend, ex husband etc. Once their through he offers her dinner. Once she leaves him and Radu take a stroll when a demon grabs radu and takes of, Kyle comes to his aid and he realizes the source of the demons is the crazy alley man from last issue. He uses his ring to restore his memories and he banishes the demons and reveals he is Felix Faust a sorcerer and that Kyle will see him again.
name: Conjuring

description:
High above Rockefeller Center, the last Green Lantern tests his mettle against the awesome magnetic powers of Doctor Polaris.

It's Christmas and Kyle is late for teen titans training and monitor duty. Arsenal chews him out and he learns the identity of all his teammates. Donna bids him goodbye to spend Christmas with her son. Kyle is left on monitor duty while his mind wonders off to Alex. He decides to take a fly around the city where he sees dr. Polaris causing trouble he defeats him and turns him over to the authorities. He gets all the love and adoration he has always wanted from the crowd so he heads back to titans tower. Donna comes back and hands him a gift, its mistletoe. And they share their first kiss.
name: Polaris

description:
"Capital Punishment" part 3, continued from GUY GARDNER: WARRIOR (1992-1996) #28. The secret organization known as Quorum unleashes a squad of super-marines on Green Lantern. Plus, Kyle gets another crack at the man who murdered his girlfriend.

Kyle is about to kill Major Force for the death of Alex when soldiers of the Quorum arrive to break things up. Him and Guy fight off the soldiers as Guy tries to reach his brother who is leading them. Kyle takes the soldiers while Guy defeats his brother who it turns out is a decoy robot. Major Force makes it back to his real brother and threatens to kill him unless he gets the ring. Guy and Kyle refuse and he kills his brother. Kyle can't bring himself to kill Major Force but Guy does.

Once it's over they discuss what happened both agreeing they dont agree but are fine with the outcome nonetheless. A mysterious man walks along the desert while Ganthet arrives on earth looking for Kyle.
name: Capital Punishment

description:
Kyle and Donna race through the stars. Kyle is in the lead on a lantern created bike while Donna in her Darkstar suit trails behind. She eventually surpasses him after shooting at him with lasers. Kyle is less than happy he lost the race but Donna says a deal is a deal. He is her slave for the day. He sets out a picnic and Donna starts talking about her custody hearing and just being glad she has Kyle in her life. Kyle chides that this picnic on Mars will surely take the weight from her shoulders.

Meanwhile on Apokalips Darkseid and his minions observe the last of the Guardians' Lanterns and decides to test this last Lantern by sending Kalibak to battle but not kill him. Kalibak eager to serve his father jumps into action.

Back on mars the lovers snuggle as Kyle promises her a carriage ride through new York. Just then via boom tube Kalibak and soldiers of Darkseid arrive. The couple get separated as Kalibak corners Kyle. He is unprepared for the ferocity of his opponent though he fights valiantly. Donna fends of the soldiers as Kyle falls before Kalibak. Deciding to disobey his father and kill the Lantern and retrieve the ring for Darkseid he is stopped by an enraged Donna who distracts him long enough for Kyle to deliver the finishing blow.

Defeated the retreat to Apokalips where Darkseid spurns Kalibak for not following his orders. Meanwhile the couple lament if they will be attacked again after the beating they gave the troops.

Outside desolation Texas a hitchhiker gets a ridehe turns out to be a returned Hal Jordan!!
name: Picnic

description:
Kyle Rayner faces his toughest challenge yet. If the neophyte Green Lantern can't find a way to defeat the mechanical monstrosity known as Duality he may loose his ring forever.

Kyle and Donna take a jog through New York and Kyle is having a hard time keeping up with the superior athletics of a longtime superhero, Titan and Amazon princess now turned Darkstar. Kyle begs her to stop, once they do they get mugged, Kyle uses his ring while Donna uses martial arts she then demonstrates to Kyle how to defend himself without the ring. He is impressed.

He offers her the cartridge ride he promised a few issues back. She has to cut though so he transforms and flies across New York then gets attacked by a monster. Kyle fights valiantly but the monster wins. Back at his apartment Ganthet reveals he sent the monster, he then tells Kyle the origins of the ring before asking him to hand it back. Kyle refuses and just then Hal Jordan walks in.
name: Ganthet's Tale Redux

description:
It's the rematch of the century as Hal Jordan, the uber-powerful Parallax, battles Kyle Rayner for the right to bear the Green Lantern power ring.

Ganthet and Hal argue about which of them should get the ring but Kyle refuses to hand it over to anyone. Hal grabs him and Kyle lashes out. Fighting ensues, Kyle is no match for Hal or thats what Ganthet thinks so he teleports away for people who stand a chance.

Martian Manhunter, Aquaman, Flash, Hawkman, Superman and Green Arrow are called. Kyle hold his own valiantly despite Hals superior power, skill and experience. In the end Kyle falls and Hal prepares to take the ring. Ganthet arrives with his team.

description:
Kyle's battle with Hal Jordan for the right to bear the Green Lantern power ring continues. Plus, Ganthet calls in some much needed help to back up the outmatched Rayner.

Hal thrashes Ganthlet's team and steals Kyle's ring. Kyle is the only one left conscious so after Ganthet and Hal have a heated argument Hal realizes he can never be GL again so he gives Kyle back the ring. Ganthet then gives Hal more power and both disappear. Green Arrow tells Kyle he earned the ring and all the heroes welcome him as Green Lantern.

Hal meanwhile is huddled in the fetal position reliving life in Central City.
name: Parallax View: The Resurrection of Hal Jordan, Part 2

description:
"The Siege of Zi Charam" part 2, continued from NEW TEEN TITANS (1984-1988) #124. Can even the combined might of Supergirl and Green Lantern rescue the New Titans from the clutches of the deadly Progenitors? Continued in DARKSTARS (1992-1996) #34.

Kyle is floating in space and Supergirl (the Matrix version) saves him and they board a nearby ship after dismantling its weaponry. Donna tries to calm down Minion telling him to allow the duo to handle things. He is hotheaded so he heads off in their direction while Donna chides herself for not being able to calm him.

On the ship the duo takes on the aliens inside while Minion fights to get to the ship. Donna is not sure what to do, assist him or follow with her plan. Matrix uses her shapshiftting to impersonate the aliens and bring in Kyle as a prisoner. They manage to infiltrate the ship and make their way to the holding cells where they rescue the captured team. Donna gets on board and they free some other aliens. Arsenal argues with Donna about not being able to handle the situation. Minion arrives badly injured and reveals to the team hes been tracked by every ship the invaders have.
name: Rescue: The Siege of the Zi Charam, Part 2

description:
Green Lantern and the Flash must team up to save their respective cities from the destructive sound powers of the new Sonar.

Kyle is fighting a man in a stolen suite of armor. He manages to save the civilians and put the villain down. He then uses his powers to give an amputee new legs before departing. Meanwhile in Keystone City the new Sonar makes his debut by destroying Keystone City hall. True to form Flash shows up since it is his city. He tries to take down the new villain but gets taken down by his powers. They tangle for a bit before sonar flies off leaving a wrecked building and a pissed Flash.

Kyle is just arriving back at his apartment and stops at Radus for some coffee; there he meets Allison a stunning red headed model. Kyle is literally left breathless by her beauty and when he goes to his apartment he gets flowers from Donna. He settles in to drawing the sunset when things shake up, literally. He suits up and finds sonar wrecking havoc. The two fight with Kyle holding his own. Just then Wally arrives telling the rookie to step aside.
name: Fast Friends?, Part 1

description:
The Scarlet Speedster and Emerald Knight must find away to work together if they're going to save their cities from the destructive power of Sonar. "Fast Friends" part 2.

Kyle and Wally start arguing immediately, Kyle is pissed at Wallys behavior while Wally just wants the rookie to step back and watch how real heroes work. While distracted they both get blasted and Sonar makes his escape.

Kyle saves Wally then Wally takes off. He saves some civilians from the villain before he gets blasted. About to be killed Kyle comes in and saves him again. They start another verbal spat which results in sonars escape. Kyle proposes they work together to save the day Wally thinks otherwise, they try to take on sonar again.

Elsewhere the man who Kyle gave ring made legs has his feet disappear. Losing his legs for a second time makes him vow revenge. The guys finally learn to work together and defeat the villain. They still dont like each other though. They part of somewhat friendly terms both thinking the other could not have saved the day without them.
name: Fast Friends? Part 2

description:
The events of Underworld Unleashed spill over into the pages of Green Lantern. Can Kyle and Donna Troy stop an amped up Mr. Freeze before the cold-hearted villain puts the city of New York on ice forever?

A mysterious man grabs a runner freezing her solid then leaving her of fall to pieces at his feet he then walks off into the night. Elsewhere Kyle tries to take care of a mod of modern day Natzi Skinheads. He gets distracted and end up at there feet, luckily Donna saves him with her darkstar power. He then cages the mob and takes his girl for a chariot ride pulled by winged horses.

The Cripple from two issues back gets a visit from neron who offers to give him back his mobility.for a price. He accepts and Neron lets him have his power.

Kyle and Donna stop at a snow filled lot and play in the snow the mysterious man turn out to be Mr. Freeze. He freezes Donna and him and kyle fight, Donna gets freed and he freezes Kyle he gets saved by neron powered Cripple who wants to kill him himself a new three way battle ensues some quick thinking and careful maneuvering has kyle use the villains to take down each other. The danger over they leave realizing this may just be the beginning.
name: Underworld Unleased

description:
An UNDERWORLD UNLEASHED tie-in! In the aftermath of his run in with the demon Neron, Kyle and Donna face the full-scale wrath of Purgatory.

Kyle arrives at his apartment beat up and bloodied, Donna tends to his wounds as he recounts what happened. He fought with neron and the demon lord tried to sway him to his cause by way of offering him the opportunity to bring Alex back from the dead. After he refuses Neon beats the snot out of him and he barley manages to leave with his life. Donna tries to tend to him but he decides he must warn the titans so they take neron out before he can get that purer soul he told Kyle about one that can only belong to Superman. He suits up and gets ready to leave.

Elsewhere the cripple who neron gave his power and gave back his legs in exchange for getting rid of Kyle, neron appears to him and tortures him until he agrees to engage kyle. He finds Kyle at home and attacks him and Donna. Kyle keeps him busy while Donna evacuates the building, she runs into a very concerned for Kyle model who kyle met a few issue back.

Kyle then defeats the man and neron takes him to hell. When firemen arrive to douse the flames Kyle is entranced by the models naked body, Donna is not pleased. Kyle then quickly departs to converge with a meeting of the justice league on the moon.
name: Bargains

description:
Tired of being a rookie, Kyle Rayner sets out on a journey to learn from the legends of the DC Universe how to be a better hero. First stop...Gotham City and a visit with the Batman Family.

Kyle comes to to get advice from Batman on how to be a hero. He manages to botch batman and robins attempted apprehension of the criminals much to Batmans dismay. Bruce ignores him and Robin gives him some words of encouragement. As Kyles chides himself for being a such a screw up and Alan shows up. He helps Allan save his wife and in return gets the advice he originally sought. Kyle continues on his journey as he departs.

In another Galaxy a Darkstar gets killed by a mysterious attacker.

description:
Kyle's next stop on his quest to become a better hero is Fawcett City for a visit with the earthly avatar of Olympic power: Captain Marvel. What can the last Green Lantern learn from a hero whose strength and abilities rival that of the Man of Steel himself?

Shazam saves a local professor from certain death after a boulder falls and almost kills him. Once the deed is done he departs. Kyle has arrived in town to see the local hero and he sketches the local art exhibit. He gets thrown out by the professor. While outside he meets with Billy Batson the civilian identity of shazam. He shares his sketches with the young man while the professor unleashes a long dead god Seti and becomes possessed by it. Kyle and Billy transform separately and do battle with the villain Kyle attacks but Shazam wants to try and talk things out. Incidentally Shazam is the one to defeat the villain with words and Kyle having learned a valuable lesson departs.

Galaxies away a slew of Darkstar related planets lay in ruins and the next projected hit is the planet Rann, John Stewart and Donna Troy plan to intercept the would be villain.
name: Hero Quest part 2: Fawcett

description:
Kyle's quest to become a better hero brings him face-to-face with the Amazing Amazon. Can Green Lantern and Wonder Woman stop a madwoman from destroying Gateway City?

Kyle and Wonder woman do battle, they want it to seem like hes a villain and hes killed her. Things play out while a galaxy away the eighteen remaining darkstars prepare to descend on Rann where they will do battle with the would-be world conqueror who has been laying waste to planets. Back on Earth Diana and Kyles plan is good and they manage to get some intergalactic criminals out of hiding. Kyle battles the female leader and wonderwoman the rest. Kyle holds back and almost gets them killed and WW saves the day. She gives kyle the final lesson of a hero, dont hold back when battle is the only choice with that she departs and Kyle gets a visit from Donna after avoiding her since their fight.
name: Hero Quest part 3: Gateway

description:
The mysterious enemy hunting the Darkstars stands revealed. Can Green Lantern and the greatest hero of Planet Rann, Adam Strange, help the interstellar police force in their darkest hour, or is this the end of the Darkstars forever?

Kyle and Donna get into it for a bit as they are still awkward around each other after their fight a few issues back. After she explains to Kyle the situation he offers to help. Back on Rann they prepare for the inevitable confrontation and Adam strange comes to assist them.

Back on the ship Kyles fills Donna in on what he was up to in her absence when they get attacked. They defend themselves.

On Rann a Darkstar is killed as the invader and his troops teleport right in and start to take down the Darkstars. He is revealed as lord Grayven and singlehandedly takes out john and Adam. Kyle and Donna finish off their assailants and rush to the planet they find the darkstars defeated and Grayven turns his attention and power to them.
name: Who Will Die?

description:
Grayven has already defeated the Darkstars and Adam Strange. Now the only thing standing between him and total victory is the last Green Lantern.

Adam Strange wakes up as Grayven starts attacking Kyle. Donna retrieves the wounded John Stewart. She gets him back to their hq and they try to give him some medical help. His heart stops. Kyle meanwhile holds of the would be Conqueror Grayven who reveals he is the bastard son of Darkseid and all the destruction, the planets and the darkstars has been to get his fathers attention and then he will usurp his fathers throne by his destruction.

Donna manages to resuscitate john and he orders them to continue their assault and defend the planet. Kyle and grayven continue to tangle and Kyle is apparently knocked out. Donna and Adam arrive on the battle filed and rally the remaining darkstars.

Grayven orders his lieutenant to find the teleporter so they can depart. Kyle arrives takes the

fight straight to Grayven. John pulls himself slowly towards the teleporter since he realizes Kyle cant beat grayven. Grayven mows down Kyle with his eye beams and john hits the teleporter it misses however BUT it gives Kyle the moment he needs to push him towards the beam and hes gone. Leaderless his lieutenant retreats. Kyle tends to John and then must try and stop the floating city from falling. Using all the knowledge he gained from Batman, Spectre, Shazam and Wonderwoman he accomplishes his task. On the battlefield the darkstars are finished Meryan and Donna quite to leave with John and Kyle respectively leaving only four darkstars active. Kyle takes everyone back to earth finally coming into his own and acknowledging hes a hero.
name: Last Stand!

description:
"Hard-Traveling Heroes: The Next Generation" part 3, continued from GREEN ARROW (1988-1998) #110. Kyle's father asks the Green Lantern for a favor--a favor that will set him against his ally Green Arrow. Continued in GREEN ARROW (1988-1998) #111.

After stopping Hatchet and breaking up the fight between he, Connor, and Kyle, the man who sent him reveals himself to be Aaron Rayner, Kyle's father. Aaron seemed both surprised and happy to see him. He asks the two to do him a favor and convinces Kyle that he wants to set up a communications satellite, but Connor is suspicious of why. Connor tries to explain his suspicions but Kyle didn't want to hear it. As soon the two of them return to earth they part ways.
name: Hard-Traveling Heroes: the Next Generation part 3

description:
All of Manhattan seems to be coming down around Green Lantern just when he has an appointment he has to keep--a date with Donna Troy.

Kyle is late for an appointment but he can't seem to get there to see the mystery woman how is wanting for him. He stops a run away train, saves a small boy from a burning building, stops an armed robbery and even rescues a cat from a tree, all the while the mystery woman waits. After a quick visit to John Stewart who is still in the hospital recovering from his battle with Grayven, Kyle recharges his ring and meets the mystery woman, Donna Troy.

The two old lovers have a long walk on the beach and discuss where there relationship went wrong. Kyle uses his ring to make Donna a necklace and promises as long as he believes in them the necklace will be solid. The last scene is the two in a kissing embrace.
name: A Beginning

description:
In the aftermath of epic events of the "Final Night," Green Lantern and the heroes of the DC Universe mourn the loss of a true hero.

This is the "Hal Jordan Funeral" issue. Writer Ron Marz and artist Darryl Banks assembled an impressive cast of DC's stars to say farewell to Green Lantern Hal Jordan in this memorable issue, available in both a regular news stand and deluxe tombstone edition, and including a second feature by writer John Broome and artist Gil Kane. After the heroes of the present day gathered in an emerald construct church to pay their respects to the life of a hero, Swamp Thing used his mastery of plant life to create a green paradise in the once desolate Coast City. With the added tribute of a green eternal flame from former Green Lantern Alan Scott, and an energy construct sculpture of Hal in his prime by the new Green Lantern Kyle Rayner, Hal's legacy was set to shine for ever.

description:
Legendary artist Jim Starlin guest-pencils a spacefaring issue of GREEN LANTERN! Kyle travels into deep space to answer a distress call, and finds its source: a floating city where robots do all the work. Corpulent overlords are disappearing, and it's at the hands of a foe that Kyle thinks may be in the right.

The story starts with our hero the whimsical Kyle Rayner blasting off to a far away planet filled with robots. Once there he is escorted to the "leader" of the place and reminisces about why the hell he's here. Turn out the pricks sent for him and demanded he come because it was his "job" as a gl to protect the universe. They even called him away from his work, you know art work! he is after all a struggling artist at this point. The leader is a "Mojo" looking alien who gives him orders like he's his lap dog. Kyle being the good guy he is goes along to hunt the would be killer of all the organic spineless a$$wipe aliens and runs into a spider creature. Kyle wraps it up and listens to things from his point of view.

The spinless schuck send in his robots to kill the creature after kyle decides against it. They tussle and kyle comes out the victor and since the spineless nit wit sent all his robots against kyle, they have no more robots left. Kyle then reveals that the spider alien was simply feeding her young and ment no ill will toward them. Spinless goes mad demanding their death. Kyle swoops them up to crry back to there planet and leav spinless to fend for himself on his barren robotless planet.
name: Servants & Masters

description:
Kyle deals with life after Donna Troy, he doesn't get much time to mope however as Grayven the son of Darseid comes knocking!

The story starts with kyle thinking about Donna troy the woman who up and left him, we learn why she did, since her son and ex husband had been killed and we also learn she left kyle not because of anything else than she thought she was bad luck and to protect him. Now I can say personally I would feel just as kyle did, unwanted, unloved, abandoned and DUMPED! those emotions came out clearly. Allison gives him a talk about how she can be there for him and they make a connection...hell! they would probably have ended up in bed if not for grayven terrorizing the city so kyle goes off to fight hm. The fight pans out all across the city till kyle kicks his ass, grayven teleports away with kyle in tow and he ends u somewhere else and gets jumped by a local mob...simply for being a green lantern!
name: Loose Ends

description:
Kyle has been swept up into a future where the Green Lantern Corps is a criminal organization. Will he be able to clear his name and get back home?

Ok folks our story opens up with The green lantern corp fleeing from the legion of superheroes. They as we find out are the worst criminals the future has encountered in quite some time. The lanterns use there powers to kick some legion ass and make off with the loot. The legion kick themselves but when they hear of a lantern in custody they drop by the jail o get him. Kyle well behaved and pleading his case of some misunderstanding gets rescued by the legion and taken to their HQ. Once there he learns that the Green Lantern corp is a group of criminals. Whats worse is he finds out Time travel has been outlawed so he cant be sent back home and as if that wasn't bad enough THEY HAVE NO RECORDS OF HIS TIME AS GREEN LANTERN!

so Kyle is left in a bad place he has no legacy...all they have is Hal Jordan records....

Being the great guy he is he soldiers on and helps the legion locate the evil corp, along the way future flash xs first with him quite openly much to his flattery yes but dismay nonetheless. The corp attacks, knocks her out and while kyle's distracted they knock him unconscious and take them aboard their base. The leader of the corp confiscates Kyle's ring but it wont work for him and it vanishes from his finger.

In an alley on earth Ganthlet the last of the guardians calls the ring to him and gives it to a young dark haired woman called Cary Wren as she places the ring on her finger she transforms into a green lantern, complete with classic costume.
name: Future Shock, part 1

description:
Future Shock continues as Kyle is trapped and taken hostage by the evil Green Lantern Corp. All this and a newly minted Green Lantern shows up to save the day! Is this the end of Kyle? Find out inside!

After the cliffhanger that was last issue we learn that the new GL a female named Cary wren is a descendant of kyle, thus why the ring works for her and our pal ganthet fills her in on everything else. Meanwhile Kyle is questioned by the leader of the lanterns about his disappearing ring. Oblivious kyle questions the authenticity of their claim to the green lantern name. Turns out each ring has a narrow range of abilities based on an energy siphon on board thanks to the location which is oan airspace.

Kyle thanks to training from Donna manages to escape but the legion members are still captive. Cary arrives to save them while the other set of legion members spring a surprise attack and a big fight plays out. we get xs and Cary together a bit right before kyle comes in and stops the siphon which causes the lanterns to be defeated.

Kyle doesn't get much time to socialize as he gets his ring back and brainiac 5 whisks him to when there should be green lanterns. The artpeice said to be one of history's greats is handed back to the museum and we get one of the most compelling shots, it was made by Kyle....entitled Sorrow.

We see kyle back in the past getting reoriented and he runs into......SINESTRO FIGHTING HAL!!!
name: Future Shock, part 2

description:
Kyle is still not home and now in the team up you never thought would happen its Kyle and Hal back to back fighting to save Oa. You don't want to miss this!

Scene opens with Kyle realizing he has clearly over jumped his return to the past. Him and Hal get locked in a yellow cage and Sinestro goes off to kill the guardians. Kyle and Hal exchange pleasantries and Kyle frees them. Along the way Kyle is hit by the epic coolness of Oa; The battery....Hal etc

Kyle's ring with no yellow weakness helps them save the guardians and Sinestro escapes, Hal and Ganthet blast Kyle for not showing more initiative and "stopping" Sinestro they question his abilities and his training which prompts Kyle to almost deck Ganthet. He explains his situation and they decide it best he stay and help out with Sinestro before going back. They track down Sinestro and Hal and Kyle take him out....well Kyle takes him out with a boxing glove to the face. Kyle is then transported back to his time, just as he is teleported Sinestro commands his ring from afar to push Hal along with Kyle. Kyle is back home but a young Hal is along for the ride.
name: In Brightest Days Past

description:
Kyle has finally made it back home, but he's not alone: a pre-Parallax Hal Jordan from the past has followed him to the present!

Its Hal like you've never seen him. Hal comes face to face with his dark future. Destroying the corps, sinking into madness, destroying Oa and the Guardians.....will these revelations cause him to go mad again?! find out inside!!!

It's the aftermath of Hal getting swept into the future along with Kyle. Young Hal is very excited for what the future will bring, Kyle of course is very somber. He cant find a way to break the "news" to Hal. While Kyle tries to find words to tell his friend about his future/fate, Hal decides to see what his beloved coast city looks like in the "future". He is shocked when he arrives to nothing........no city...just vacant land.

Hal completely freaks out at the realization that his city is gone. Once he calms down Kyle reveals his fate....going rogue after the city's destruction and destroying the corp, trying to remake time etc. His eventual death reigniting the sun and how Coast city was made his "memorial" site. Hal listens to the whole thing and then blows up on Kyle, the revelations leave him so emotional he destroys his memorial statue and fly's off. Kyle doesn't follow he allows Hal to sort out his feeling on his own.

Hal full of all kinds of emotions saves a bus load of crippled children and when the teacher calls him an angel for saving them, his "hope" is reignited. This heroic deed allows him to reconcile his emotions and he returns to Kyle. They have a small talk about how they can get him back to his rightful place in time and checking in with the JLA.

On apocalypse Desad tricks the oh so smart Kalibak to attack Hal, he agrees and Desad's plan is sealed.
name: Emerald Knights Part 1: Coming To Terms

description:
A pre-Parallax Hal Jordan from the past is now trapped in the present. It is at this moment that the deadly son of Darkseid, Kalibak, decides to strike.

A time lost Hal continues to reintegrate with a life he didn't even have. Adjustments are hard...but now he must face the ferocity of Kalibak!

The story picks up with Kyle helping Hal get reoriented with his "future". Hal has got the whole story of how he went crazy and killed everyone and destroyed the corps, tried to set Time right etc etc blah blah. John and Guy are both happy but terrified of his return especially with the prospect this Hal is younger than them and doesn't even know them. He opts to leave the guys in the lantern lounge to go somewhere he actually feels attached to.

A Ferris airfield Carol and another friend of Hal's reminisce about the good old days when Hal was around. Of course young Hal arrives and Carol throws her arms and lips around him. Young Hal is shocked as he hasn't developed that kind of relationship with Carol yet. After reminiscing Kalibak of apocalypse attacks and Hal eventually defeats him but vows revenge.

Hal then comes to the realization that since he's here he may as well make the best of it, him and his friends end the issue together.
name: Emerald Knights, Part 2

description:
Hal Jordan rejoins the Justice League, but not everyone is happy to see Hal back. Plus, where does this leave Kyle Rayner?

Hal Jordan rejoins the JLA! Where does that leave Kyle? Feeling pretty down and ready to quit this whole superhero gig. He's comforted by Jade and, well, you'll have-to find out.....

Kyle takes Hal to visit/meet the JLA. while there the members fall all over each other to make hal feel welcome and they offer him membership right there on the spot. Flash chides Kyle for being knocked down the totem pole by Hal until Kyle opts to leave the watchtower since apparently he's not wanted. He then saves some people from falling rubble though his mind is fixed on the fact that Hal may have just taken his place on the team.

At home he's comforted by Jen and after an emotional outburst both find solace in the others arms ( they end up sleeping together). After Jen leaves the bedroom for the kitchen Batman tells Kyle that he is still the JLA green lantern and that Hal was given membership at his behest because he does not trust him. He also confides in kyle that he trusts him just as the JLA does with his very life. With that batman disappears and Jen and kyle snuggle under the cover.
name: Emerald Knights, Part 3

description:
Oliver Queen and Hal Jordan were best friends. Now a pre-Parallax Hal Jordan from the past must team up with his dead friend's son to face the group that killed the original Green Arrow.

Young Hal and Green Arrow Connor hawk bond over their capture by the Eden corps, a bunch of Hippie tree hungers who incidentally had killed Connor's dad, Oliver Queen. One of their captors is Hal's old military test pilot buddy, now turned mercenary named Hardy. We learn why a big shot pilot like Hal ended up working for Feris aircraft after he was honorably discharged from the military test pilot gig because hardy tried to steal their plane and it crashed, he disappeared and Hal was used as scapegoat to explain everything away.

Hardy taunts the guys while the Eden Corps get ready to bomb Oliver Queen's city with the guys still attached to the Bomb. Hardy has Hal's ring which he plans to sell to the highest bidder once its all over. He's working with the Eden corp for money. In the end the guys go free get back the ring, stop the bombing and reminiscence in front of Oliver Queen's grave. Hal is duly sad as he wasn't even given the chance to bond with Oli since he's from BEFORE they were friends.

Continued from Green Arrow #136
name: Emerald Knights Part 4: Greener Pastures Conclusion

description:
John Stewart and Guy Gardner are taken down by the last person they ever expected to see again. Plus, Hal finally comes face-to-face with the nightmare he is destined to become.

Kyle arrives at warriors, the green lantern lounge to find it in shambles. He finds a beat up Guy and John who tell him parallax destroyed the place looking for his younger self. We flash back to what happened earlier with Parallax fighting John and Guy, guy uses his Vuldarian power and John those strange bursts of green energy. Guy saves John when he realizes that Young Hal and Parallax are two different people as strange as that sounds, he tells parallax where where to find himself and then they have a finale duel. Parallax won and flew off for the watchtower on the moon.

Kyle decides to stop parallax before he reaches Hal, on the watchtower Jonn and Hal wax philosophical about starts before Jonn departs for his quarters leaving Hal to the stars.

Kyle reaches Parallax and they fight, though parallax doesn't remember Kyle, he's from a time before he met Kyle or was defeated, he's come to return Hal to his proper time so he can ensure his existence. Kyle realizes the gravity of the situation, if he stops parallax, Hal doesnt destroy the corp, he doesn't get the ring and worst Hal never dies reigniting the sun thus saving their universe. Kyle calls a truce but Parallax knocks him unconscious so he can finish his job. Just then Young Hal arrives ready to fight Parallax.
name: Emerald Knights Part 5: Haunted By the Past

description:
Hal Jordan faces the sins of his past (or future, as the case may be). It's Hal Jordan vs. Parallax, with Kyle Rayner stuck in the middle!

Hal battles Parallax in defense of Kyle, Parallax pleads with Hal to return to his time so that he can ensure his creation, Hal refuses and lashes out with his powers. He apparently defeats Parallax and rushes to Kyles side. Parallax then teleports them all through time right to a second before coast city was destroyed. He shows Hal the bombs descending as they walk through coast city as time stands still. Hal is scared of becoming parallax thus he continues to refuse to go back.

They fight until Kyle jumps in and tells them both that time is in danger unless they all go back to when they are supposed to. They all reluctantly agree none more so than Hal. He hugs Kyle goodbye and give him something. They then lock rings as Hals ring erases there memories and Parallax send them all back to their proper time. As they leave coast city is annihilated.

Parallax arrives in the past to knock superman out, Hal defeats Sinestro on his own and Kyle tells the whole thing to Jenny. After they talk he reveals what Hal gave to him. An old school Green Power Ring.
name: Emerald Knights Part 6: Time's Up

description:
Green Lantern must team up with the dubious duo of Booster Gold and Plastic Man to stop a secret organization from obtaining a mysterious package.

A mysterious package is accidentally delivered to Kyle's apartment, and its owner--surprisingly enough, a super-villain --- will do anything to get it back. It seems like your typical super-hero fun and games until Plastic Man is captured. Now GL and Booster may have to sacrifice the package's contents to save Plastic life!
name: The Package

And in this state, what will happen when he reaches the homebase of the universe-meddling race ? the Controllers?

Can he gain the trust of the cutthroat inmate in time to save the ex-Mrs. Undertow's life? And what's the real story behind Undertow's demise??
